# Frontend styling conventions

- Use Emotion for styling React components.
- Use `useStyles2(getStyles)` for theme-aware style memoization.
- Keep `getStyles` at the end of the file.
- Prefer `@grafana/ui` layout primitives before adding custom wrapper styles.
- Compose conditional classes with Emotion `cx` instead of branching style builders.
- Keep Emotion class keys `camelCase`.
- Avoid SASS for new/edited frontend code; migrate touched SASS areas toward Emotion.

Primary references:
- `contribute/style-guides/styling.md`
- `contribute/style-guides/frontend.md`
